(5) Agreed to exclude from the coverage of a CW ban munitions and devices for dissemination of
                            irritants—see, however, para B(2)
                            below;

(7) Accepted in principle the concept of joint inspection teams, but with
                            reservation regarding the type of OSI
                            it would apply to and the composition and authority of such teams;

(2) Remained unwilling to accommodate the U.S. position on irritants in a
                            satisfactory manner, asserting that they could not agree to legalizing
                            unilateral reservations to the Geneva Protocol;

(5) Rejected the distinction between “implementation” and “compliance” as
                            based on the U.S. concept of verification, which they did not
                            accept;
